narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, good L4 class with a reasonable workload.
Take Professor Cividane's class if you placed into L4.
Definitely! I actually liked going to this class, even though it was every day. There is a steady flow of work, but it's really not much, and your language skills will improve immensely.
Don't take it unless you take it with Ame Cividanes, she makes the course.
I would definitely recommend taking this class.
I would recommend this course. My Spanish listening and compositions skills have especially improved.
There is a lot of speaking required in this class, which is something to take into consideration if a student is hesitant or shy about speaking Spanish in front of others.
If you want to get better at Spanish, take it of course. If you just want to get past the distribution requirement, you still have to take it.
